   <br/>
   COVERED WAGON:
   <br/>
   You can use a "classifier-3" handshape to show a vehicle. Then you 
can use a flat handshape to show the covering.
   <br/>
   This concept would only be clear if you had already established some 
context by indicating the horses up front.
   <br/>
   Another, even better method would be to spell W-A-G-O-N, then show 
the classifier-3, do the cover, then show the horses up front, thus 
starting with the largest main object.
   <br/>
   <br/>
